data.content:
Organization
The organization aims to improve its pricing optimization system.

Pricing Optimization Project
A project focused on improving a pricing optimization system by consolidating data, identifying optimal time windows, and creating operational reports.

Pricing Optimization System
A system that currently relies on automatic rebookings and specific alerts for pricing optimization, with limitations in data analysis and historical/competitive data usage.

Automatic Rebookings
A current method used by the pricing optimization system, which analyzes files one by one.

Specific Alerts
A current method used by the pricing optimization system, which analyzes files one by one.

Logs
Raw data that needs to be joined and structured for the pricing optimization project.

Bookings
Raw data that needs to be joined and structured for the pricing optimization project.

Operational Report
A report to be created by the pricing optimization project for use by teams.

Price Drop Opportunities
Opportunities detected by the current pricing optimization system as they happen, without prioritization or grouping.

Automated Workflow
A workflow to be developed by the pricing optimization project to join and structure data, isolate optimizations, analyze gains, identify opportunities, and distribute results.

Status S
A status used to isolate relevant optimizations within the data.

Gains
Information to be analyzed and used for optimization, extracted from cdv_log_operation.lgop_results.

Itineraries
Information to be analyzed for optimization.

Development Environment
The environment for developing the optimization script, initially using .csv extracts and later connecting to an API.

Database Extracts
Provided in .csv format for development simplification.

API
To be connected to for data retrieval once the optimization script is ready, providing data in an identical format to the .csv files.<SEP>An interface for real data retrieval, which becomes available during the project timeline.<SEP>API is a method for data ingestion, contrasting with CSVs.

cdv_log_operation.csv
A file containing logs, used for data joining.<SEP>A CSV database file representing a portion of the total data to be processed.

cdv_wnj_air_booking_view.csv
A file containing bookings, used for data joining.<SEP>A CSV database file representing a portion of the total data to be processed.

cdv_log_operation.lgop_element_id
A join key for merging log operations and booking data.

cdv_wnj_air_booking_view.wbkg_reference
A join key for merging log operations and booking data.

Optimization Datetimes
Data to be calculated after joining log operation and booking tables.

cdv_log_operation.lgop_status
A field used for filtering records, where status 'S' indicates relevant optimizations.

cdv_log_operation.lgop_when
The field representing the Optimization Datetime.<SEP>A column in the cdv_log_operation table that contains optimization datetimes.

cdv_wnj_air_booking_view.dair_code
The field representing the Airline.

cdv_wnj_air_booking_view.FromAirportCode
The field representing the Start of Trip.

cdv_wnj_air_booking_view.ToAirportCode
The field representing the End of Trip.

cdv_wnj_air_booking_view.wbkg_start_date
The field representing the Travel Dates.

cdv_log_operation.lgop_results
The field from which Gain is extracted.

Analytical Aggregation
A process to sort records by airline and identify best gains based on trip details.

listeOptimisation_dd-MM-yyyy.csv
The generated CSV file name for the optimization list.

Exemple rapport optimisation.xlsx
An example Excel file used as a reference for filling the generated CSV.<SEP>An Excel file used as a template for filling in required data for optimization reports.

Nuanced Time Analysis
A further analysis step after extracting best gains for each airline.

File Sharing
The document explicitly states that it may not be shared in any form outside the scope of the project's development.

Pricing Optimization System Limitations
The current pricing optimization system is limited because it analyzes files one by one, lacks a global view, and doesn't use historical or competitive data.

Data Volume
The data volume is approximately 1GB once connected to the API.

CSV Format
Database extracts are provided in .csv format for development simplification.

API Data Format
The API will provide data in an identical format to the .csv files.

Optimization Script
A script that needs to be developed and will eventually connect to an API for data.

Data Joining Process
The process involves joining cdv_log_operation.csv (logs) and cdv_wnj_air_booking_view.csv (bookings) using a specific join key.

Record Filtering Process
A process to keep only rows where cdv_log_operation.lgop_status = 'S'.

Data Extraction for Calculations
The process of extracting specific fields for calculations, including Optimization Datetime, Airline, Start of Trip, End of Trip, Travel Dates, and Gain.

Analytical Aggregation Process
A process that involves sorting records by airline and keeping records with the best gains under specific identical conditions, or keeping the row if conditions are not identical.

CSV File Generation
The process of generating a CSV file named listeOptimisation_dd-MM-yyyy.csv.

Excel File Reference
Exemple rapport optimisation.xlsx is an example Excel file used as a reference for filling the generated CSV.

Nuanced Time Analysis Process
A process that follows the extraction of best gains for each airline, aiming for further optimization.

topOptimisation.json
A JSON file where the results of the optimization analysis are saved.

cdv_log_operation.md
An architecture file for the cdv_log_operation database.

cdv_wnj_air_booking_view.md
An architecture file for the cdv_wnj_air_booking_view database.

Python
The required technology for this project.

SFTP
A space where CSV and JSON files must be deposited.

GMT+1
A time zone specification for depositing files.

Pricing Optimization
The name of the project or document.

September 3-5, 2025
The dates for Phase 0 - Project Launch.

September 8-26, 2025
The dates for Phase 1 - Development.

September 15, 2025
The date when the API for real data retrieval becomes available.

September 16, 2025
The date for a project meeting with the client to validate API connection and progress.

September 17-19, 2025
The dates for Phase 3 - Advanced Feature Development.

September 29 - October 2, 2025
The dates for Phase 4 - Finalization.

Airline
Airlines are entities for which optimization gains are to be extracted and analyzed.

Average Gains
A metric calculated to understand trends in optimization, broken down by time of day, day of the week, and combined day+hour.

Time of Day
A factor used to analyze average gains, with examples like 'around 3 a.m.' indicating potential for better gains.

Day of the Week
A factor used to analyze average gains, with examples like 'Tuesday is more favorable than Friday'.

Combined Day + Hour
A detailed factor for analyzing average gains, representing 7x24 combinations (e.g., Monday at 10 a.m.).

Ranking Slots
A process to sort optimization results by average gain in descending order for each grouping (hour, day, day+hour) and keep the top 3.

JSON Output
The format in which the results of the optimization analysis are to be saved.

CSV Files
Files that must be deposited on an SFTP space, representing a portion of the total data volume.

Data Provision
Information regarding the databases provided to facilitate development.

Development Timeline
A schedule outlining the phases and key dates for the project.

Local Development Environment
The environment that needs to be set up for development.

Data Schemas
Information about the structure of the data, which needs to be verified and compared between CSV and API.

Unit and Performance Tests
Tests to be run on a significant amount of data during the finalization phase.<SEP>Unit and performance tests are to be run on approximately 1 GB of data during Phase 4.

CSVs
CSVs are a format for data ingestion, to be compared with API ingestion.

Phase 4 - Finalization
Phase 4 - Finalization is a project phase scheduled from September 29 to October 2, 2025, involving unit and performance tests and adjustments based on client feedback.

Phase 5 - Delivery and Final Acceptance
Phase 5 - Delivery and Final Acceptance is a project phase scheduled for October 3, 2025, involving putting the application into production and final acceptance.

API becomes available

Production delivery
Production delivery is a key milestone scheduled for October 3.

Pipeline

Schema Compatibility
Schema compatibility needs to be verified between CSV and API data ingestion methods.

Application
The application is to be put into production on the client's environment.

Client's Environment
The client's environment is where the application will be put into production.

Server Configuration
Server configuration is handled by the client.

Final Acceptance
Final acceptance is the concluding step of Phase 5.

Development
Development is scheduled to start with example files on September 3.

Example Files
Example files will be used at the start of development.
